Variable names starting with `let` or `var` when placed after the first parameter break the syntax highlight. Note: I'm in a typescript file.

```
var let2 = 0;
var f = function(a,b,c){};
f(0,let2,'test');   //breaks

var var2 = 0;
var f = function(a,b,c){};
f(0,var2,'test');   //breaks

var function2 = 0;
var f = function(a,b,c){};
f(0,function2,'test');  //works
```

renders as

![](http://puu.sh/nyCrO.png)

